233
00:18:55,589 --> 00:19:01,869
 And that, in fact, is processing that is done with a discrete time system.

234
00:19:02,269 --> 00:19:09,329
 So when you hear referred to, let's say, in stock market reports, a 51-day moving average,

235
00:19:09,670 --> 00:19:16,470
 that, in fact, is processing the stock market index with a particular discrete time system.

236
00:19:16,849 --> 00:19:24,869
 The result of doing that on this particular example generates a smooth version of the curve,

237
00:19:24,869 --> 00:19:26,109
 which I overlay here.

238
00:19:26,509 --> 00:19:33,309
 And the overlay then is really attempting to track the

239
00:19:34,130 --> 00:19:37,430
 smoother variations and de-emphasize the more rapid

